ir names. Custom card types that you add to your Wagn will, unless [[http://www.wagn.org/wagn/formatting|formatted]], look and act like Basic cards.</p>'),(4841,'2011-02-15 21:39:42',406,150,'<p>Number cards can contain only numerical values.</p>'),(4842,'2011-02-15 21:41:54',407,150,'<p>PlainText cards are for unstyled text, and offer a simpler edit  interface with just a few lines of space (although their content can be  longer). [[Phrase]] cards are identical but their edit interface is only one line tall.</p>'),(4843,'2011-02-15 21:43:07',408,150,'<p>Phrase cards are for unstyled text, and offer an edit  interface simpler than [[Basic]] cards, and just one line tall. [[PlainText]] cards are identical except their edit interface offers a few lines.</p>'),(4845,'2011-02-15 21:43:45',407,150,'<p>PlainText cards are for unstyled text, and offer an edit  interface simpler than [[Basic]] cards, and just a few lines tall (although their content can be  longer). [[Phrase]] cards are identical but their edit interface is only one line tall.</p>'),(4846,'2011-02-15 21:44:09',409,150,'<p>Date cards contain a date.</p>'),(4847,'2011-02-15 21:58:33',154,150,'[[Ethan McCutchen]]\n[[John Abbe]]\n[[Lewis Hoffman]]\n[[*ignore]]\n[[cards to copy to new Wagns]]\n[[new]]\n[[all non-star cards]]\n[[cards by type]]\n[[Cardtype descriptions]]\n[[Basic+*watchers]]\n[[related subtabs - universal]]\n[[Settings values]]\n[[not set or setting]]\n[[*cssmobile]]\n[[translatable cards]]\n[[default cards]]\n[[star cards]]'),(4848,'2011-02-15 21:58:43',410,150,'<p>Since so many capabilities are built with Wagn itself, new  installations come with several hundred cards by default. Most of them  are listed here (not including many [[plus cards]] made up of the cards  below), and the default cards themselves are actually maintained on  en.dwagn.org</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Cardtypes]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Administrative<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Account Request]]</p>\n<p>[[Cardtype]]</p>\n<p>[[Role]]</p>\n<p>[[Set]]</p>\n<p>[[Setting]]</p>\n<p>[[User]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Data types</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Basic]]<br>[[Phrase]]<br>[[PlainText]]<br>[[Image]]<br>[[File]]</p>\n<p>[[Pointer]]</p>\n<p>[[Search]]</p>\n<p>[[Toggle]]<br>[[Number]]<br>[[Date]]<br>[[HTML]]</p>\n<p>[[Ruby]] - but off by default</p>\n<p>[[Script]] - but off by default</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Menu]]<br>[[Administrator links]]<br>[[Config]] - in Administrator links</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Roles and Accounts<br></h2>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Anyone]]<br>[[Anyone signed in]]<br>[[Administrator]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[Anonymous]]</p>\n<p>[[Wagn Bot]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Other<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[cards with accounts]] - used on [[*account]]<br>[[Invite Success]] - See [[/wagn/account#Administering%20accounts]] for more on this and the next two.<br>[[Request Sent]]<br>[[Signup Success]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>For ordering searches</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>So that you can do things like [[User+*type+by create]] (people in the order they registered an account).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[by name]]<br>[[by update]]<br>[[by create]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Home]] - default front page<br>[[discussion]] - [[plus cards|plussing]] any card to this makes a card that allows comments.<br>[[tag]] - for tagging, e.g. in the [[Related tab]]</p>\n<p>[[description]] - for the built in descriptions of cardtypes and roles<br>[[Default Layout]] - see [[custom layouts]]<br>[[email config]] - used by the [[flexible email]] system<br>[[Form submission thanks]] - see [[thank you messages]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Star cards]] (everything below)<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{star cards}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(4849,'2011-02-15 21:58:58',411,150,'<p>Some [[card]] names begin with a star. This is currently used to distinguish cards that are either (or both):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>referred to in Wagn\'s code - to alert coders to that</li>\n<li>integral to Wagn\'s default structure, and possibly using a name that  we don\'t want to \"take\" from the main name space - the idea is also for  the star to cue users to be careful about editing them</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here they are, sorted by function, and noted if they are not in code. There\'s also an <strong>alphabetical list of [[all star cards]]</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Config|Site configuration]]</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*title]]</li>\n<li>[[*home]]</li>\n<li>[[*logo]]</li>\n<li>[[*css]]</li>\n<li>[[*favicon]]</li>\n<li>[[*sidebar]] (not in code)</li>\n<li>[[*tinyMCE]]</li>\n<li>[[*google analytics key]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Account]]-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*invite, *signup and *request explain &amp; include the following  configuration cards for different account-granting processes. (Not all  of these cards exist by default, but there are reasonable in-code  defaults.)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*invite]] &mdash; [[*invite+*subject]], [[*invite+*message]], [[*invite+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*signup]] &mdash; [[*signup+*subject]], [[*signup+*message]], [[*signup+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*request]] &mdash; [[*request+*to]], [[*request+*thanks]]</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*account]] lists existing accounts and [[account requests]], and is used for the \"account\" subtab under the Related tab.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*accountable]] is a setting (see below), but is also account-related.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are normal [[searches]] (i.e., not in code):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*editing+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*editing]] to see cards they have edited.</li>\n<li>[[*editors+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a card to [[*editors]] to see accounts that have edited it.</li>\n<li>[[*watching+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*watching]] to see cards they are [[notification|watching]].</li>\n<li>[[*watchers+*right+*default]] (Pointer) &mdash; plus a card to [[*watchers]] to see/edit accounts that are watching it.</li>\n<li>[[*roles+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*roles]] to see the roles that account has.</li>\n<li>[[*members+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a role card to&nbsp;[[*members]] to see the accounts with that role.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Sets]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The search forms themselves are nothing special, but the extra  interface you see on set cards (*all, *options+*right, etc.) is added in  code.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*all]]</li>\n<li>[[*right]] &mdash; [[*right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type]] &mdash; [[*type+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type plus right]] &mdash; [[*type plus right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*self]] &mdash; [[*self+*right+*content]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Settings]]<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Settings sorted}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Mail-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are used by the [[flexible email]] system, and for   [[/wagn/Config#Email / Account Configuration|account-related emails]]   people receive.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from]], [[*to]], [[*cc]], [[*bcc]]</li>\n<li>[[*subject]]</li>\n<li>[[*message]]</li>\n<li>[[*attach]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related subtabs</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Only *related is mentioned in code, but all of these cards are  integral to the Related tab, and should not be messed with unless you   know what you\'re   doing.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*related]] &mdash; a Pointer, determining the subtabs that appear on  every card. It can also be plussed to any Cardtype card, to point to a  subtab you want to have appear on cards of that type. See [[/Related  tab#How%20To|how to customize Related subtabs]].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Default subtabs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*incoming+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that [[linking|link]] to or  [[inclusion|include]] this card; and cards that are tagged with this  card</li>\n<li>[[*outgoing+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that this card links to or includes; and cards that this card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*plusses+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] that this card is the  left or right side of; and the other parts of those plus cards</li>\n<li>[[*community+*right+*content]] &mdash; who has edited this card; who is  watching the card; this card\'s +discussion card; and cards that this  card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*account+*right+*content]] &mdash; the [[roles]] that this [[account]]  has, and cards that this account is  watching or has edited (this subtab  only  appears on [[User]] cards, and  any other cards associated with  an account).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related searches<br></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are generally useful for finding related cards, and are used in  the default subtabs (as are the account-related searches such as  +*editing, listed above):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*links+*right+*content]] &mdash; what this card [[linking|links]] to</li>\n<li>[[*linkers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that link to this card (aka backlinks)</li>\n<li>[[*inclusions+*right+*content]] &mdash; card [[inclusion|included]] in this card</li>\n<li>[[*includers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that include this card</li>\n<li>[[*plus cards+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] of which this is a part</li>\n<li>[[*plus parts+*right+*content]] &mdash; the other parts of plus cards this card is a part of</li>\n<li>[[*tagged+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards tagged with this card</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Virtual cards]]</h1>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Note that none of these will show up in search results.</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>[[*now]] &mdash; shows the current date/time, e.g.: {{*now}}</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>Used in [[Default Layout]]</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*head]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes in layout\'s HTML head</li>\n<li>[[*navbox]] &mdash; the [[Search bar]]</li>\n<li>[[*account_link]] &mdash; links to sign in/out, current user\'s card, and inviting people or requesting an account</li>\n<li>[[*version]] &mdash; version information of running Wagn software, goes in [[*sidebar]]</li>\n<li>[[*alert]] &mdash; where [[alerts]] will show up</li>\n<li>[[*foot]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes just before /body on page\'s HTML</li>\n</ul>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>[[Searches]]<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*recent changes]] &mdash; used for http://wagn.org/recent</li>\n<li>[[*search]] &mdash; similar to a [[form]], used for [[Search bar]] results</li>\n<li>[[*broken_link]] &mdash; cards that have links to cards that don\'t yet exist</li>\n</ul>'),(4851,'2011-02-15 22:00:23',154,150,'[[Ethan McCutchen]]\n[[John Abbe]]\n[[Lewis Hoffman]]\n[[*ignore]]\n[[cards to copy to new Wagns]]\n[[new]]\n[[all non-star cards]]\n[[cards by type]]\n[[Cardtype descriptions]]\n[[Basic+*watchers]]\n[[related subtabs - universal]]\n[[Settings values]]\n[[not set or setting]]\n[[*cssmobile]]\n[[translatable cards]]\n[[default cards]]\n[[star cards]]\n[[not listed yet]]'),(4852,'2011-02-15 22:03:15',412,150,'{\"found_by\": \"all non-star cards\",\n \"not\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"default cards\"}\n}'),(4856,'2011-02-15 22:04:38',412,150,'{\"found_by\": \"all non-star cards\",\n \"not\": {\"or\": \"referred_to_by\": \"default cards\",\n                    \"links\": \"ignore\",\n                    \"right\": \"description\"\n           }\n}'),(4858,'2011-02-15 22:05:03',412,150,'{\"found_by\": \"all non-star cards\",\n \"not\": {\"or\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"default cards\",\n                      \"links\