te>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*account]] lists existing accounts and [[account requests]], and is used for the \"account\" subtab under the Related tab.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*accountable]] is a setting (see below), but is also account-related.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are normal [[searches]] (i.e., not in code):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*editing+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*editing]] to see cards they have edited.</li>\n<li>[[*editors+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a card to [[*editors]] to see accounts that have edited it.</li>\n<li>[[*watching+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*watching]] to see cards they are [[notification|watching]].</li>\n<li>[[*watchers+*right+*default]] (Pointer) &mdash; plus a card to  [[*watchers]] to see/edit accounts that are watching it. (And  [[*watchers+*right+*options]] to restrict autocomplete to Users.</li>\n<li>[[*roles+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*roles]] to see the roles that account has.</li>\n<li>[[*members+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a role card to&nbsp;[[*members]] to see the accounts with that role.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Sets]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The search forms themselves are nothing special, but the extra  interface you see on set cards (*all, *options+*right, etc.) is added in  code.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*all]]</li>\n<li>[[*right]] &mdash; [[*right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type]] &mdash; [[*type+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type plus right]] &mdash; [[*type plus right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*self]] &mdash; [[*self+*right+*content]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Settings]]<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Settings sorted}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Settings defaults and edit help<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Settings defaults and help|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*all+*accountable]] &mdash; no, meaning most cards cannot be accounts. (This is overridden for User cards.)</p>\n<p>[[*all+*default]] &mdash; sets the default [[card type|type]] of new cards to be [[Basic]].</p>\n<p>[[*all+*layout]] &mdash; sets the default layout for all cards. See [[custom layouts]].</p>\n<p>[[*all+*table of contents]] &mdash; defaults to 0, meaning no [[tables of contents]] will be generated.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*option label]] &mdash; defaults +*options labels to be drawn from those labels\' +description cards. See [[Pointer]].</p>\n<p>[[*layout+*right+*options]] &mdash; restricts autocomplete of +*layout to HTML cards.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Mail-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are used by the [[flexible email]] system, and for   [[/wagn/Config#Email / Account Configuration|account-related emails]]   people receive.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from]], [[*to]], [[*cc]], [[*bcc]]</li>\n<li>[[*subject]]</li>\n<li>[[*message]]</li>\n<li>[[*attach]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Configuring those:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from+*right+*default]], [[*to+*right+*default]],  [[*cc+*right+*default]], [[*bcc+*right+*default]],  [[*subject+*right+*default]] &mdash; Phrase</li>\n<li>[[*attach+*right+*default]] &mdash; Pointer (which will point to File cards to send as attachments)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related tab</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Only *related and *account+*related are mentioned in code, but all of  these cards are integral to the Related tab, and should not be messed  with unless you  know what you\'re   doing.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*related]] &mdash; points to the subtabs that appear on every card. It  can also be plussed to any Cardtype card, to point to a subtab you want  to have appear on cards of that type. See [[/Related tab#How%20To|how to  customize Related subtabs]].</p>\n<p>[[*related+*right+*default]] &mdash; defaults *related to be a Pointer</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Default subtabs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*incoming+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that [[linking|link]] to or  [[inclusion|include]] this card; and cards that are tagged with this  card</li>\n<li>[[*outgoing+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that this card links to or includes; and cards that this card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*plusses+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] that this card is the  left or right side of; and the other parts of those plus cards</li>\n<li>[[*community+*right+*content]] &mdash; who has edited this card; who is  watching the card; this card\'s +discussion card; and cards that this  card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*account+*right+*content]] &mdash; the [[roles]] that this [[account]]  has, and cards that this account is  watching or has edited. This subtab   appears on [[User]] cards (and  any other cards associated with an  account), because it is pointed to by [[*account+*related]].</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related searches<br></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are generally useful for finding related cards, and are used in  the default subtabs (as are the account-related searches such as  +*editing, listed above):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*links+*right+*content]] &mdash; what this card [[linking|links]] to</li>\n<li>[[*linkers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that link to this card (aka backlinks)</li>\n<li>[[*inclusions+*right+*content]] &mdash; card [[inclusion|included]] in this card</li>\n<li>[[*includers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that include this card</li>\n<li>[[*plus cards+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] of which this is a part</li>\n<li>[[*plus parts+*right+*content]] &mdash; the other parts of plus cards this card is a part of</li>\n<li>[[*tagged+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards tagged with this card</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Virtual cards]]</h1>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Note that none of these will show up in search results.</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>[[*now]] &mdash; shows the current date/time, e.g.: {{*now}}</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>Used in [[Default Layout]]</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*head]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes in layout\'s HTML head</li>\n<li>[[*navbox]] &mdash; the [[Search bar]]</li>\n<li>[[*account_link]] &mdash; links to sign in/out, current user\'s card, and inviting people or requesting an account</li>\n<li>[[*version]] &mdash; version information of running Wagn software, goes in [[*sidebar]]</li>\n<li>[[*alert]] &mdash; where [[alerts]] will show up</li>\n<li>[[*foot]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes just before /body on page\'s HTML</li>\n</ul>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>[[Searches]]<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*recent changes]] &mdash; used for http://wagn.org/recent</li>\n<li>[[*search]] &mdash; similar to a [[form]], used for [[Search bar]] results</li>\n<li>[[*broken_link]] &mdash; cards that have links to cards that don\'t yet exist</li>\n</ul>'),(4908,'2011-02-16 01:24:12',404,150,'<p>Here are all of the cards to translate into another language. Be sure not to edit the name of any cards that begin with a star (*), or their content unless you are explicitly asked to do so here:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Cardtypes<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Cardtype <strong>names</strong> themselves should be translated (in code they use codename, so that\'s okay, yes?), as well as the <strong>description</strong> of each Cardtype that has one:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*type+by name}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Edit help<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>All of the customizable edit help <strong>contents</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*edit help+*right+by name}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>names</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of these cards in the sidebar:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Menu|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Administrator links|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Config|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>description</strong> of each role and user:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Anyone|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Anyone signed in|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Administrator|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Anonymous|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Wagn Bot|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> of \"cards with accounts\" and the <strong>content</strong> of \"*account\".</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{cards with accounts|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*account|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of these:</p>\n<blockquote>{{Invite Success|closed}}\n<p>{{Request Sent|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Signup Success|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <strong>content</strong> of these. Make sure you update the reference at the end of the first three to the corresponding new name of one of the three cards just above.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*invite|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*request|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*signup|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Role+*type+*default|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related tab\'s subtabs</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>content</strong> only of these:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*incoming+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*outgoing+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*plusses+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*community+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*account+*right+*content|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{watcher instructions for related tab+*right+*content|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Cardtype+watcher instructions for related tab+*type plus right+*content|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{watcher instructions for related tab|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> of the default home card &mdash; make sure to change both the name of the card itself, and update *home to the new name:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Home|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*home|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Similarly, change both the <strong>name</strong> of \"Default Layout\" and the reference to it in \"*all+*layout\":</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Default Layout|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*all+*layout|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just the <strong>names</strong> of these cards, used to order search results:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{by name|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{by update|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{by create|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of this card:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Form submission thanks|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>names</strong> only of these cards:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{discussion|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{tag|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{description|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{email config|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(4909,'2011-02-16 02:07:33',411,150,'<p>Some [[card]] names begin with a star. This is currently used to distinguish cards that are either (or both):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>referred to in Wagn\'s code - to alert coders to that</li>\n<li>integral to Wagn\'s default structure, and possibly using a name that  we don\'t want to \"take\" from the main name space - the idea is also for  the star to cue users to be careful about editing them</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here they are, sorted by function, and noted if they are not in code. There\'s also an <strong>alphabetical list of [[all star cards]]</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Config|Site configuration]]</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*title]]</li>\n<li>[[*home]]</li>\n<li>[[*logo]]</li>\n<li>[[*css]]</li>\n<li>[[*favicon]]</li>\n<li>[[*sidebar]] (not in code), and [[*sidebar+*self+*edit help]] to document it</li>\n<li>[[*tinyMCE]]</li>\n<li>[[*google analytics key]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Account]]-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*invite, *signup and *request explain &amp; include the following  configuration cards for different account-granting processes. (Not all  of these cards exist by default, but there are reasonable in-code  defaults.)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*invite]] &mdash; [[*invite+*subject]], [[*invite+*message]], [[*invite+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*signup]] &mdash; [[*signup+*subject]], [[*signup+*message]], [[*signup+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*request]] &mdash; [[*request+*to]], [[*request+*thanks]]</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*account]] lists existing accounts and [[account requests]], and is used for the \"account\" subtab under the Related tab.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*accountable]] is a setting (see below), but is also account-related.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are normal [[searches]] (i.e., not in code):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*editing+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*editing]] to see cards they have edited.</li>\n<li>[[*editors+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a card to [[*editors]] to see accounts that have edited it.</li>\n<li>[[*watching+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*watching]] to see cards they are [[notification|watching]].</li>\n<li>[[*watchers+*right+*default]] (Pointer) &mdash; plus a card to  [[*watchers]] to see/edit accounts that are watching it. (And  [[*watchers+*right+*options]] to restrict autocomplete to Users.</li>\n<li>[[*roles+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*roles]] to see the roles that account has.</li>\n<li>[[*members+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a role card to&nbsp;[[*members]] to see the accounts with that role.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Sets]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The search forms themselves are nothing special, but the extra  interface you see on set cards (*all, *options+*right, etc.) is added in  code.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*all]]</li>\n<li>[[*right]] &mdash; [[*right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type]] &mdash; [[*type+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type plus right]] &mdash; [[*type plus right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*self]] &mdash; [[*self+*right+*content]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Settings]]<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Settings sorted}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Settings defaults and edit help, etc.<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Settings defaults and help|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*layout+*right+*options]] &mdash; restricts autocomplete of +*layout to HTML cards.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Setting values<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*all+*accountable]] &mdash; no, meaning most cards cannot be accounts. (This is overridden for User cards.)</p>\n<p>[[*all+*captcha]] &mdash; no, meaning [[captcha]] is off by default for all cards.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*default]] &mdash; sets the default [[card type|type]] of new cards to [[Basic]].</p>\n<p>[[*all+*layout]] &mdash; sets the default layout for all cards. See [[custom layouts]].</p>\n<p>[[*all+*table of contents]] &mdash; defaults to 0, meaning no [[tables of contents]] will be generated.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*option label]] &mdash; defaults +*options labels to be drawn from those labels\' +description cards. See [[Pointer]].</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Mail-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are used by the [[flexible email]] system, and for   [[/wagn/Config#Email / Account Configuration|account-related emails]]   people receive.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from]], [[*to]], [[*cc]], [[*bcc]]</li>\n<li>[[*subject]]</li>\n<li>[[*message]]</li>\n<li>[[*attach]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Configuring those:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from+*right+*default]], [[*to+*right+*default]],  [[*cc+*right+*default]], [[*bcc+*right+*default]],  [[*subject+*right+*default]] &mdash; sets type to Phrase</li>\n<li>[[*attach+*right+*default]] &mdash; sets type to Pointer</li>\n<li>[[*attach+*right+*options]] &mdash; autocompletes and autocreates cards that any +*attach points to to be [[File]] cards</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related tab</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Only *related and *account+*related are mentioned in code, but all of  these cards are integral to the Related tab, and should not be messed  with unless you  know what you\'re   doing.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*related]] &mdash; points to the subtabs that appear on every card. It  can also be plussed to any Cardtype card, to point to a subtab you want  to have appear on cards of that type. See [[/Related tab#How%20To|how to  customize Related subtabs]].</p>\n<p>[[*related+*right+*default]] &mdash; defaults cards plussed to *related to be a Pointer</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Default subtabs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*incoming+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that [[linking|link]] to or  [[inclusion|include]] this card; and cards that are tagged with this  card</li>\n<li>[[*outgoing+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that this card links to or includes; and cards that this card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*plusses+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] that this card is the  left or right side of; and the other parts of those plus cards</li>\n<li>[[*community+*right+*content]] &mdash; who has edited this card; who is  watching the card; this card\'s +discussion card; and cards that this  card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*account+*right+*content]] &mdash; the [[roles]] that this [[account]]  has, and cards that this account is  watching or has edited. This subtab   appears on [[User]] cards (and  any other cards associated with an  account), because it is pointed to by [[*account+*related]].</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related searches<br></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are generally useful for finding related cards, and are used in  the default subtabs (as are the account-related searches such as  +*editing, listed above):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*links+*right+*content]] &mdash; what this card [[linking|links]] to</li>\n<li>[[*linkers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that link to this card (aka backlinks)</li>\n<li>[[*inclusions+*right+*content]] &mdash; card [[inclusion|included]] in this card</li>\n<li>[[*includers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that include this card</li>\n<li>[[*plus cards+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] of which this is a part</li>\n<li>[[*plus parts+*right+*content]] &mdash; the other parts of plus cards this card is a part of</li>\n<li>[[*tagged+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards tagged with this card</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Virtual cards]]</h1>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Note that none of these will show up in search results.</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>[[*now]] &mdash; shows the current date/time, e.g.: {{*now}}</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>Used in [[Default Layout]]</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*head]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes in layout\'s HTML head</li>\n<li>[[*navbox]] &mdash; the [[Search bar]]</li>\n<li>[[*account_link]] &mdash; links to sign in/out, current user\'s card, and inviting people or requesting an account</li>\n<li>[[*version]] &mdash; version information of running Wagn software, goes in [[*sidebar]]</li>\n<li>[[*alert]] &mdash; where [[alerts]] will show up</li>\n<li>[[*foot]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes just before /body on page\'s HTML</li>\n</ul>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>[[Searches]]<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*recent changes]] &mdash; used for http://wagn.org/recent</li>\n<li>[[*search]] &mdash; similar to a [[form]], used for [[Search bar]] results</li>\n<li>[[*broken_link]] &mdash; cards that have links to cards that don\'t yet exist</li>\n</ul>'),(4910,'2011-02-16 02:07:52',410,150,'<p>Since so many capabilities are built with Wagn itself, new  installations come with several hundred cards by default. Most of them  are listed here (not including many cards that make up some of the plus  cards below). The default cards themselves are actually maintained on  en.dwagn.org</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Card types]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Administrative<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Account Request]]</p>\n<p>[[Cardtype]]</p>\n<p>[[Role]]</p>\n<p>[[Set]]</p>\n<p>[[Setting]]</p>\n<p>[[User]] &mdash; and [[User+*type+*accountable]] makes it possible for them to have accounts.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Data types</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Basic]]<br>[[Phrase]]<br>[[PlainText]]<br>[[Image]] &mdash; and [[Image+*right+*default]] makes any new card ending in +Image to be of type Image.<br>[[File]]</p>\n<p>[[Pointer]]</p>\n<p>[[Search]]</p>\n<p>[[Toggle]]<br>[[Number]]<br>[[Date]]<br>[[HTML]] &mdash; and [[HTML+*type+*default]] sets new ones to be editable only by Administrators.</p>\n<p>[[Ruby]] &mdash; but they\'re turned off by default</p>\n<p>[[Script]] &mdash; but they\'re turned off by default</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Menu]]<br>[[Administrator links]]<br>[[Config]] &mdash; in Administrator links</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Roles and Accounts<br></h2>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Anyone]]<br>[[Anyone signed in]]<br>[[Administrator]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[Anonymous]]</p>\n<p>[[Wagn Bot]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Other<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[cards with accounts]] &mdash; lists account-holding cards (typically [[Users]], included on [[*account]]<br>[[Invite Success]] &mdash; See [[/wagn/account#Administering%20accounts]] for more on this and the next two.<br>[[Request Sent]]<br>[[Signup Success]]</p>\n<p>[[Role+*type+*content]] &mdash; form for Role cards</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>For ordering searches</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>So that you can do things like [[User+*type+by create]] (people in the order they registered an account).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[by name]]<br>[[by update]]<br>[[by create]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>[[Home]] &mdash; default front page</li>\n<li>[[email config+*right+*content]] &mdash; form for emails sent via [[flexible email]]. Help text is [[email config+*right+*edit help]].</li>\n<li>[[discussion+*right+*default]] &mdash; so that any [[plus card]] ending with +[[discussion]] allows comments<br>[[tags]] &mdash; for tagging, e.g. in the [[Related tab]]. [[tags+*right+*default]] makes any card +tags a Pointer</li>\n<li>[[Form submission thanks]] &mdash; see [[thank you messages]]</li>\n<li>[[description]] &mdash; for the built in descriptions of cardtypes and roles<br>[[Default Layout]] &mdash; the default layout, specified by [[*all+*layout]]. See [[custom layouts]].</li>\n<li>Regarding [[notifications]]:<br> {{watcher instructions for related tab|closed}}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Star cards]] (everything below)<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{star cards}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(4913,'2011-02-16 02:11:13',376,150,''),(4914,'2011-02-16 02:11:13',417,150,'4'),(4915,'2011-02-16 02:12:11',374,150,''),(4916,'2011-02-16 02:12:11',418,150,'4'),(4917,'2011-02-16 02:14:32',362,150,'{\"not\":{\"or\":{\"type\":[\"in\",\"Set\",\"Setting\"], \"left\":{\"type\":\"Set\"}, \"right\": \"description\", \"referred_to_by\":\"*ignore\"}},\n \"sort\": \"name\", \"limit\": \"200\"}'),(4918,'2011-02-16 02:15:12',360,150,'{\"left\":{\"type\":\"Set\"}, \"right\":{\"type\":\"Setting\"},\n \"sort\": \"name\" \n}'),(4919,'2011-02-16 02:15:44',360,150,'{\"left\":{\"type\":\"Set\"}, \"right\":{\"type\":\"Setting\"},\n \"limit\": \"200\",\n \"sort\": \"name\"\n}'),(4921,'2011-02-16 03:30:22',405,150,'<p>Basic cards are for rich text, and it is the default type for new cards. Therefore (unlike cards of other types) Basic cards are not labeled with their type next to their names. Custom card types that you add to your Wagn will, unless [[http://www.wagn.org/wagn/formatting|formatted]], look and act like Basic cards.</p>'),(4927,'2011-02-16 03:36:01',404,150,'<p>Here are all of the cards to translate into another language. Be sure not to edit the name of any cards that begin with a star (*), or their content unless you are explicitly asked to do so here:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Cardtypes<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Cardtype <strong>names</strong> themselves should be translated (in code they use codename, so that\'s okay, yes?), as well as the <strong>description</strong> of each Cardtype that has one:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*type+by name}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Edit help<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>All of the customizable edit help <strong>contents</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*edit help+*right+by name}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>names</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of these cards in the sidebar:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Menu|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Administrator links|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Config|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>description</strong> of each role and user:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Anyone|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Anyone signed in|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Administrator|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Anonymous|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Wagn Bot|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> of \"cards with accounts\" and the <strong>content</strong> of \"*account\".</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{cards with accounts|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*account|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of these:</p>\n<blockquote>{{Invite Success|closed}}\n<p>{{Request Sent|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Signup Success|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <strong>content</strong> of these. Make sure you update the reference at the end of the first three to the corresponding new name of one of the three cards just above.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*invite|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*request|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*signup|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Role+*type+*default|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related tab\'s subtabs</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>content</strong> only of these:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*incoming+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*outgoing+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*plusses+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*community+*right+*content|closed}}<br>{{*account+*right+*content|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{watcher instructions for related tab+*right+*content|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Cardtype+watcher instructions for related tab+*type plus right+*content|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{watcher instructions for related tab|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> of the default home card &mdash; make sure to change both the name of the card itself, and update *home to the new name:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Home|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*home|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Similarly, change the <strong>name</strong> of \"Default Layout\" and the reference to it in \"*all+*layout\". Also, translate Home and Recent and the credit text in the <strong>content</strong> of \"Default Layout\":</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Default Layout|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*all+*layout|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just the <strong>names</strong> of these cards (used to order search results):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{by name|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{by update|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{by create|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>name</strong> and <strong>content</strong> of this card:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Form submission thanks|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <strong>names</strong> only of these cards:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{discussion|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{tag|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{description|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{email config|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(4928,'2011-02-16 03:45:02',53,150,'width: \'100%\',\nauto_resize : true,\nrelative_urls: false,\ntheme : \"advanced\",\ntheme_advanced_buttons1 : \"formatselect,bold,italic,separator,\"\n+ \"blockquote,bullist,numlist,hr,separator,\"\n+ \"code\",                         \ntheme_advanced_buttons2 : \"\",                         \ntheme_advanced_buttons3 : \"\",                         \ntheme_advanced_path : false,                         \ntheme_advanced_toolbar_location : \"top\",  \ntheme_advanced_toolbar_align : \"left\", \ntheme_advanced_resizing : true,\ntheme_advanced_resize_horizontal : false,                      \ntheme_advanced_statusbar_location : \"bottom\",\ntheme_advanced_blockformats : \"p,h1,h2\",\ncontent_css : \'/stylesheets/defaults.css,/*css.css\',\nextended_valid_elements : \"a[name|href|target|title|onclick],\"\n+ \"img[class|src|border=0|alt|title|hspace|vspace|width|height|\"\n+ \"align|onmouseover|onmouseout|name],hr[class|width|size|noshade],\"\n+ \"font[face|size|color|style],span[class|align|style]\"          \n'),(4930,'2011-02-16 09:30:51',411,150,'<p>Some [[card]] names begin with a star. This is currently used to distinguish cards that are either (or both):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>referred to in Wagn\'s code - to alert coders to that</li>\n<li>integral to Wagn\'s default structure, and possibly using a name that  we don\'t want to \"take\" from the main name space - the idea is also for  the star to cue users to be careful about editing them</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here they are, sorted by function, and noted if they are not in code. There\'s also an <strong>alphabetical list of [[all star cards]]</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Config|Site configuration]]</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*title]]</li>\n<li>[[*home]]</li>\n<li>[[*logo]]</li>\n<li>[[*css]]</li>\n<li>[[*favicon]]</li>\n<li>[[*sidebar]] (not in code), and [[*sidebar+*self+*edit help]] to document it</li>\n<li>[[*tinyMCE]]</li>\n<li>[[*google analytics key]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Account]]-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*invite, *signup and *request explain &amp; include the following  configuration cards for different account-granting processes. (Not all  of these cards exist by default, but there are reasonable in-code  defaults.)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*invite]] &mdash; [[*invite+*subject]], [[*invite+*message]], [[*invite+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*signup]] &mdash; [[*signup+*subject]], [[*signup+*message]], [[*signup+*thanks]]</li>\n<li>[[*request]] &mdash; [[*request+*to]], [[*request+*thanks]]</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*account]] lists existing accounts and [[account requests]], and is used for the \"account\" subtab under the Related tab.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*accountable]] is a setting (see below), but is also account-related.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are normal [[searches]] (i.e., not in code):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*editing+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*editing]] to see cards they have edited.</li>\n<li>[[*editors+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a card to [[*editors]] to see accounts that have edited it.</li>\n<li>[[*watching+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*watching]] to see cards they are [[notification|watching]].</li>\n<li>[[*watchers+*right+*default]] (Pointer) &mdash; plus a card to  [[*watchers]] to see/edit accounts that are watching it. (And  [[*watchers+*right+*options]] to restrict autocomplete to Users.</li>\n<li>[[*roles+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus an account card to [[*roles]] to see the roles that account has.</li>\n<li>[[*members+*right+*content]] &mdash; plus a role card to&nbsp;[[*members]] to see the accounts with that role.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Sets]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The search forms themselves are nothing special, but the extra  interface you see on set cards (*all, *options+*right, etc.) is added in  code.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*all]]</li>\n<li>[[*right]] &mdash; [[*right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type]] &mdash; [[*type+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*type plus right]] &mdash; [[*type plus right+*right+*content]]</li>\n<li>[[*self]] &mdash; [[*self+*right+*content]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Settings]]<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Settings sorted}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Settings defaults and edit help, etc.<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Settings defaults and help|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*layout+*right+*options]] &mdash; restricts autocomplete of +*layout to HTML cards.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Setting values<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*all+*accountable]] &mdash; no, meaning most cards cannot be accounts. (This is overridden for User cards.)</p>\n<p>[[*all+*captcha]] &mdash; no, meaning [[captcha]] is off by default for all cards.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*default]] &mdash; sets the default [[permissions]] of new cards.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*layout]] &mdash; sets the default layout for all cards. See [[custom layouts]].</p>\n<p>[[*all+*table of contents]] &mdash; defaults to 0, meaning no [[tables of contents]] will be generated.</p>\n<p>[[*all+*option label]] &mdash; defaults +*options labels to be drawn from those labels\' +description cards. See [[Pointer]].</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Mail-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are used by the [[flexible email]] system, and for   [[/wagn/Config#Email / Account Configuration|account-related emails]]   people receive.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from]], [[*to]], [[*cc]], [[*bcc]]</li>\n<li>[[*subject]]</li>\n<li>[[*message]]</li>\n<li>[[*attach]]</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Configuring those:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*from+*right+*default]], [[*to+*right+*default]],  [[*cc+*right+*default]], [[*bcc+*right+*default]],  [[*subject+*right+*default]] &mdash; sets type to Phrase</li>\n<li>[[*attach+*right+*default]] &mdash; sets type to Pointer</li>\n<li>[[*attach+*right+*options]] &mdash; autocompletes and autocreates cards that any +*attach points to to be [[File]] cards</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Related tab</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Only *related and *account+*related are mentioned in code, but all of  these cards are integral to the Related tab, and should not be messed  with unless you  know what you\'re   doing.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*related]] &mdash; points to the subtabs that appear on every card. It  can also be plussed to any Cardtype card, to point to a subtab you want  to have appear on cards of that type. See [[/Related tab#How%20To|how to  customize Related subtabs]].</p>\n<p>[[*related+*right+*default]] &mdash; defaults cards plussed to *related to be a Pointer</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Default subtabs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*incoming+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that [[linking|link]] to or  [[inclusion|include]] this card; and cards that are tagged with this  card</li>\n<li>[[*outgoing+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that this card links to or includes; and cards that this card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*plusses+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] that this card is the  left or right side of; and the other parts of those plus cards</li>\n<li>[[*community+*right+*content]] &mdash; who has edited this card; who is  watching the card; this card\'s +discussion card; and cards that this  card is tagged with</li>\n<li>[[*account+*right+*content]] &mdash; the [[roles]] that this [[account]]  has, and cards that this account is  watching or has edited. This subtab   appears on [[User]] cards (and  any other cards associated with an  account), because it is pointed to by [[*account+*related]].</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related searches<br></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are generally useful for finding related cards, and are used in  the default subtabs (as are the account-related searches such as  +*editing, listed above):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*links+*right+*content]] &mdash; what this card [[linking|links]] to</li>\n<li>[[*linkers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that link to this card (aka backlinks)</li>\n<li>[[*inclusions+*right+*content]] &mdash; card [[inclusion|included]] in this card</li>\n<li>[[*includers+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards that include this card</li>\n<li>[[*plus cards+*right+*content]] &mdash; [[plus cards]] of which this is a part</li>\n<li>[[*plus parts+*right+*content]] &mdash; the other parts of plus cards this card is a part of</li>\n<li>[[*tagged+*right+*content]] &mdash; cards tagged with this card</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Virtual cards]]</h1>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Note that none of these will show up in search results.</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>[[*now]] &mdash; shows the current date/time, e.g.: {{*now}}</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>Used in [[Default Layout]]</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*head]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes in layout\'s HTML head</li>\n<li>[[*navbox]] &mdash; the [[Search bar]]</li>\n<li>[[*account_link]] &mdash; links to sign in/out, current user\'s card, and inviting people or requesting an account</li>\n<li>[[*version]] &mdash; version information of running Wagn software, goes in [[*sidebar]]</li>\n<li>[[*alert]] &mdash; where [[alerts]] will show up</li>\n<li>[[*foot]] &mdash; <strong>required</strong>, goes just before /body on page\'s HTML</li>\n</ul>\n<div><br></div>\n<h2>[[Searches]]<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[[*recent changes]] &mdash; used for http://wagn.org/recent</li>\n<li>[[*search]] &mdash; similar to a [[form]], used for [[Search bar]] results</li>\n<li>[[*broken_link]] &mdash; cards that have links to cards that don\'t yet exist</li>\n</ul>'),(4934,'2011-02-16 09:32:16',412,150,'{\"not\": {\"or\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"default cards\",\n                      \"linked_to_by\": \"star cards\",\n                      \"type\": \"Setting\",\n                      \"found_by\": \"Settings defaults and help\",\n                      \"right\": \"description\",\n                      \"part\": \"*right\"}\n           },\n \"limit\": \"200\",\n \"sort\": \"name\"\n}'),(4935,'2011-02-16 09:35:39',410,150,'<p>Since so many capabilities are built with Wagn itself, new  installations come with several hundred cards by default. Most of them  are listed here (not including many cards that make up some of the plus  cards below). The default cards themselves are actually maintained on  en.dwagn.org</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Cardtypes]]</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Administrative<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Account Request]]</p>\n<p>[[Cardtype]]</p>\n<p>[[Role]]</p>\n<p>[[Set]]</p>\n<p>[[Setting]]</p>\n<p>[[User]] &mdash; and [[User+*type+*accountable]] makes it possible for them to have accounts.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Data types</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Basic]]<br>[[Phrase]]<br>[[PlainText]]<br>[[Image]] &mdash; and [[Image+*right+*default]] makes any new card ending in +Image to be of type Image.<br>[[File]]</p>\n<p>[[Pointer]]</p>\n<p>[[Search]]</p>\n<p>[[Toggle]]<br>[[Number]]<br>[[Date]]<br>[[HTML]] &mdash; and [[HTML+*type+*default]] sets new ones to be editable only by Administrators.</p>\n<p>[[Ruby]] &mdash; but they\'re turned off by default</p>\n<p>[[Script]] &mdash; but they\'re turned off by default</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Menu]]<br>[[Administrator links]]<br>[[Config]] &mdash; in Administrator links</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account-related</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Roles and Accounts<br></h2>\n<p>Each includes a description card, and links here to relevant documentation.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Anyone]]<br>[[Anyone signed in]]<br>[[Administrator]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[Anonymous]]</p>\n<p>[[Wagn Bot]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Other<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[cards with accounts]] &mdash; lists account-holding cards (typically [[Users]], included on [[*account]]<br>[[Invite Success]] &mdash; See [[/wagn/account#Administering%20accounts]] for more on this and the next two.<br>[[Request Sent]]<br>[[Signup Success]]</p>\n<p>[[Role+*type+*content]] &mdash; form for Role cards</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>For ordering searches</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>So that you can do things like [[User+*type+by create]] (people in the order they registered an account).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[by name+*right+*content]]<br>[[by update+*right+*content]]]]<br>[[by create+*right+*content]]]]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>[[Home]] &mdash; default front page</li>\n<li>[[email config+*right+*content]] &mdash; form for emails sent via [[flexible email]]. Help text is [[email config+*right+*edit help]].</li>\n<li>[[discussion+*right+*default]] &mdash; so that any [[plus card]] ending with +[[discussion]] allows comments<br>[[tags]] &mdash; for tagging, e.g. in the [[Related tab]]. [[tags+*right+*default]] makes any card +tags a Pointer</li>\n<li>[[Form submission thanks]] &mdash; see [[thank you messages]]</li>\n<li>[[description]] &mdash; for the built in descriptions of cardtypes and roles<br>[[Default Layout]] &mdash; the default layout, specified by [[*all+*layout]]. See [[custom layouts]].</li>\n<li>Regarding [[notifications]]:<br> {{watcher instructions for related tab|closed}}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>[[Star cards]] (everything below)<br></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{star cards}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(4976,'2011-02-16 09:54:17',152,150,'<p><em><span>Cards and [[images]] in this Wagn are copied to new Wagns</span></em>. Exceptions should be added here:</p>\n<p>{{*ignore|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This one updates automatically:</p>\n<p>{{cards to copy to new Wagns|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>What comprises those cards</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Set+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Settings+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Setting values| closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{cardtype descriptions|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Role+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*account]], [[WagnBot]], [[Anonymous]]</p>\n<p>[[*to]], [[*from]], [[*thanks]], [[Invite Success]], [[Signup  Success]], [[Request Sent]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[Config]]</p>\n<p>{{Config+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*sidebar+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related tab</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*account+*right+*content]] - available on any card that has the account extension</p>\n<p>Available on every card, because they\'re in [[*related]]:</p>\n<p>{{Related subtabs - universal|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote></blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Cards useful for Wagneering</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[by name+*right+*content]]</p>\n<p>[[by update+*right+*content]]</p>\n<p>[[by create+*right+*content]]</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Everything about default Wagns that can be done within cards happens here. Make changes that make sense to you, and watch what each other are doing on Recent. There\'s space for discussion at the bottom of this page if you like.</li>\n<li>If you remove stuff from [[Config]] that may still be relevant later, add it to http://www.wagn.org/wagn/English_Wagn+not_ready </li>\n<li>For changes/additions here to show up in already-existing Wagns, put a note in the next [[http://www.wagn.org/wagn/Release|Wagn release]]\'s discussion about which cards you want migrated.</li>\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions|Permissions are specified on wagn.org]], because we want people to be able to choose different initial setups.</li>\n<li>Everything that involves code should be ticketed on wagn.org.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Todo</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Content / Wagneering<br></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Adapt or include [[default cards]] for the \"What comprises...\" section above.</li>\n<li>Test and tweak http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions (ongoing)</li>\n<li>make *ignore a Search that returns Users, Account Requests, and things referred to by *ignore+tag. (Requires changing the dump a little, but could bring new users in with less overhead.)&nbsp; <em>eventually.&nbsp;&nbsp; not ready for this yet --efm</em></li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Documentation<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>When documenting tickets that relate to [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Installation+tickets_for_item|installation]] or [