 Google Analytics]]</em></div>\r\n<div>Â </div>\r\n<div>Â </div>\r\n</blockquote>'),(6527,'2013-08-07 22:01:19',80,149,'<div>{{+original}}</div>'),(6528,'2013-08-07 22:01:23',800,149,''),(6529,'2013-08-07 22:01:23',801,149,''),(6530,'2013-08-07 22:01:48',801,149,'<h1>Create</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. For the Organizing Artist</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>DRY: Don\'t Repeat Yourself. Â Most projects wind up with data copied all over the place: on the website, in a database, in email, etc. Â Wagn helps you organize data for use and reuse in many different contexts. When you update it once, you update it everywhere.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Website</h2>\r\n<p>Fully customizable [[http://wagn.org/layouts|layouts]] and [[http://wagn.org/views|views]] help you present information flexibly and beautifully.  <em>[[Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Database</h2>\r\n<p>Whether organizing a database for an open collaborative community, a private team, or something in between, Wagn\'s powerful [[http://wagn.org/types|typing]], [[http://wagn.org/compound_names|compound names]], [[http://wagn.org/formatting|formatting]], and native [[http://wagn.org/WQL|query language]] comprise quite a toolset. <em>[[Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Workflow</h2>\r\n<p>Web submissions, project proposals, meeting records, customer info, research, sketches, reports... Â They\'re all interconnected in our minds, and they should be digitally, too. Â Wagn helps teams create and evolve their information flows in fluid and adaptive ways. <em>[[Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>Explore</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. How Pioneers Roll.</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>Wagneers don\'t have worry about breaking things. All configuration is in cards, and all cards have revision histories.  Deleting cards doesn\'t really destroy them permanently, it just adds them to the trash. Â So all configuration can be reviewed and, if necessary, reversed.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Cards</h2>\r\n<p>In Wagn it\'s all in the [[http://wagn.org/cards|cards]]. All text, files, images, accounts, and everything is stored in a card. If a card has fields, the fields are cards, too. <em>[[http://wagn.org/cards|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Types</h2>\r\n<p>Every card on Wagn has a \"[[http://wagn.org/type|type]]\". [[http://wagn.org/users|Users]], [[http://wagn.org/image|Images]], and [[http://wagn.org/search|Searches]] are just a few of the types that come with Wagn out of the box. And you can create your own types to organize and structure your data. <em>[[http://wagn.org/type|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Navbox</h2>\r\n<p>It\'s a search bar, an auto-completer, and a shortcut for creating new cards. <em>[[http://wagn.org/navbox|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Menus</h2>\r\n<p>In Wagn, there\'s no separate \"Admin Area\". Everything you administer is accessed right in place with no context shift through convenient [[http://wagn.org/menus|menus]]. <em>[[http://wagn.org/menus|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Rules</h2>\r\n<p>The heart of configuring Wagn is creating [[http://wagn.org/rules|rules]].  Accessed via the \"advanced\" menu item, rules control every aspect of a card\'s behavior and appearance, from [[http://wagn.org/permissions|permissions]] to [[http://wagn.org/formatting|formatting]] to [[http://wagn.org/help_text|help text]] and beyond. <em>[[http://wagn.org/rules|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>Collaborate</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. Go Together</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>Any interface you don\'t use is noise. Wagn keeps edit interface quiet for those who just want to read, and it keeps configuration interface quiet for those who just want to edit content.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Accounts</h2>\r\n<p>Central to any web community is the question of how contributors gain accounts. New Wagn installs have an invitation-based model, but access can be made as open or closed as desired. <em>[[http://wagn.org/accounts|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Permissions</h2>\r\n<p>An elegant [[http://wagn.org/permissions|permissions]] system allows fine-grained control over who can create, read, update, and delete. <em>[[http://wagn.org/permissions|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Evolution</h2>\r\n<p>Even the greatest web technology can\'t guarantee great community.  That requires thoughtfully adapting technology to community needs. Wagn is designed to evolve with you. <em>[[Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>'),(6531,'2013-08-07 22:02:07',795,149,'<p>[[http://wagn.org/Features| Features]]</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/cards|cards]]</li>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/types|types]]</li>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/rules|rules]]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/Syntax Reference| Syntax]]</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/link_syntax|links]]</li>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/inclusion_syntax|inclusions]]</li>\r\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/WQL_syntax|queries]]</li>\r\n</ul>'),(6532,'2013-08-07 22:04:40',198,149,'/* line 2, ../../app/assets/stylesheets/home.scss */\r\n.SELF-home-original > .content ul {\r\n  list-style-type: none;\r\n  margin: 1em;\r\n  padding: 0;\r\n}\r\n/* line 7, ../../app/assets/stylesheets/home.scss */\r\n.SELF-home-original > .content li {\r\n  padding: .8em;\r\n  margin: 0;\r\n  background: #eeeeee;\r\n}\r\n/* line 12, ../../app/assets/stylesheets/home.scss */\r\n.SELF-home-original > .content li:nth-child(even) {\r\n  background: #ddd;\r\n}\r\n/* line 15, ../../app/assets/stylesheets/home.scss */\r\n.SELF-home-original > .content h1 {\r\n  font-size: 1.5em;\r\n  padding: 0.6em 0 0.3em 0;\r\n}\r\n/* line 19, ../../app/assets/stylesheets/home.scss */\r\n.SELF-home-original > .content aside {\r\n  float: right;\r\n  border: 1px solid #999;\r\n  background: white;\r\n  width: 33%;\r\n  padding: 1em;\r\n  margin: 36px 16px 2px 5px;\r\n  overflow: auto;\r\n  border-radius: 18px;\r\n  text-align